    "recap_url": "https://www.upstatespartans.com/news/2026/3/21/brent-stukes-turns-in-career-long-outing-with-career-best-nine-strikeouts-as-baseball-falls-in-extras-at-longwood",
    "recap_headline": "University of South Carolina Upstate Athletics",
    "recap_text": "FARMVILLE, Va. \u2013\nHeading to extra innings for the first time this season, USC Upstate baseball fell on the wrong side of the decision in a game that featured an identical final score to the night prior, 5-4, Saturday afternoon against Longwood.\nTaking the bump for the Spartans, junior right-handed pitcher\nBrent Stukes\nturned in the longest start by an Upstate pitcher this season, tossing 7.0 frames while striking out nine, both career highs. In relief, redshirt freshman right-hander\nJacob Kirby\nsecured his eighth scoreless outing of the campaign, working 2.0 innings with one strikeout. Redshirt junior righty\nMax Eichenberger\npunched out two in his 0.2 innings of work.\nUsing a pair of productive outs, a sac fly and RBI groundout, redshirt sophomore catcher\nTyler Lang\nnotched the Spartans' lone multi-RBI game, driving home two. From the leadoff spot, redshirt sophomore centerfielder\nHenry Zenor\npicked up two hits, the lone multi-hit game for Upstate.\nGame Information\nScore: Longwood 5; USC Upstate 4 [10 inn.]\nRecords: USC Upstate (12-12; 3-2 Big South); Longwood (16-7; 2-3 Big South)\nLocation: Buddy Bolding Stadium | Farmville, Va.\nHow It Happened\nB1: Scratching the game's first run for the second straight contest, Longwood scored on a Jae'den Carter groundout to first, scoring Brogan Jones from third.\nB2: Taking advantage of an Upstate fielding error, the Lancers pushed across a pair, staking a three-run lead after the second.\nT3: Providing an instant response, Upstate scored thrice in the third. Ripping a single through the right side,\nHenry Zenor\nplated the first before consecutive sac flies from\nTyler Lang\nand\nJohnny Sweeney\ntied the game.\nB7: Breaking a 3-3 deadlock, Max Lawson slugged a solo shot to left for the Lancers.\nT8: Battling back to tie the game for the Spartans,\nTyler Lang\ndrove home the tying run with a groundout to short.\nB10: Busting the deadlock, Lucas Johnson doubled home the game-winning run as he lifted a ball just out of the reach of the Upstate outfield in right-center.\nNotable\nStriking out nine hitters Saturday,\nBrent Stukes'\ncareer-high strikeout count marked the highest single-game total for a Spartan pitcher this season. He bests\nMax Kaplan\n(seven versus Western Carolina) and\nChris Torres\n(seven versus Texas) for the mark this year while his total marks the best single-game total by a Spartan since\nAmp Phillips\nstruck out nine versus Clemson on May 30, 2025.\nWorking 7.0 innings for Upstate, Stukes's start marked the longest by a Spartan starting pitcher this season. His start is the longest by an Upstate starter since May 22, 2025, when\nAmp Phillips\ntossed a complete game against Winthrop.\nWorking 2.0 scoreless innings Saturday,\nJacob Kirby\nsecured his eight scoreless outing of the season, leading all Upstate pitchers. Last season, only two Spartans,\nBraden Consaul\nand\nCooper Ellingworth\n, worked more scoreless outings with 12 and 11, respectively.\nHeading to extras Saturday, the game marked the first since a 15-inning game on April 18, 2025, versus UNCG to see Upstate play extra frames.\nConnect with the Spartans\nFacebook.com/UpstateAthletics\nTwitter | @UpstateBSB | @UpstateSpartans\nInstagram | @UpstateBSB | @UpstateSpartans\nYouTube.com/UpstateSpartans\nINVEST IN CHAMPIONS\n- Join the Upstate Athletic Fund (UAF) and enjoy enhanced benefits for your support of all USC Upstate programs! Make your gift today,\nclick here\n!",
